documentation.text:
The UniswapOracleFactory contract is designed to produce individual UniswapOracleInstance contracts
This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from
Ownable.sol*

The UniswapOracleFactory contract is designed to produce individual UniswapOracleInstance contracts
This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from
Ownable.sol*

params.factory: is the address of the uniswap factory
params.tokenA: is the address of the first token in the token pair for this oracle
params.tokenB: is the addresss of the second token in the token pair for this oracle*

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

createNewOracle(address,address,address).notice: createNewOracle allows the owner of this contract to deploy a new oracle contract when a new asset is whitelisted

userdoc.notice: The UniswapOracleFactory contract is designed to produce individual UniswapOracleInstance contracts This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from Ownable.sol*
